_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_

**Catch reopen refresh failures before clearing the pending flag.**

This clears `pendingRefreshRef.current` before the async refresh succeeds, and `void debouncedListDirectory(...)` has no error path. A transient list failure here loses the deferred refresh permanently until another filesystem event arrives.

<details>
<summary>Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
 useEffect(() => {
   if (isOpen && pendingRefreshRef.current) {
     pendingRefreshRef.current = false;
     log('[CodePreviewPanel] panel opened with pending refresh, triggering now');
     const currentPath = filesystemCurrentPathRef.current || filesystemScopePathRef.current || 'project';
-    void debouncedListDirectory(normalizeProjectPath(currentPath));
+    void debouncedListDirectory(normalizeProjectPath(currentPath)).catch((error) => {
+      pendingRefreshRef.current = true;
+      logError('[CodePreviewPanel] failed to flush deferred refresh', error);
+    });
   }
-}, [isOpen]);
+}, [isOpen, debouncedListDirectory, normalizeProjectPath, logError]);
```
</details>
As per coding guidelines "Do not swallow errors silently; include enough context in logs to debug failures without logging secrets or credentials" and "Use `try/catch` in new async code when failure needs custom logging, cleanup, or a typed fallback".

